Detailed Description

cvmx_usbdrd::_uahc_gsbuscfg0

This register can be used to configure the core after power-on or a change in mode of operation. This register mainly contains AXI system-related configuration parameters. Do not change this register after the initial programming. The application must program this register before starting any transactions on AXI. When [INCRBRSTENA] is enabled, it has the highest priority over other burst lengths. The core always performs the largest burst when enabled.

This register can be reset by IOI reset or with USBDRD()_UCTL_CTL[UAHC_RST].
